<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Learning on Elbow Hotpot</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/tags/learning/</link><description>Recent content in Learning on Elbow Hotpot</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/tags/learning/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Claude Code CLI Orchestration via --print Mode</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/claude-code-cli-orchestration/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/claude-code-cli-orchestration/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Using nanobot to drive Claude Code programmatically as a coding sub-agent. Yes, we&amp;rsquo;re building AI inception. Tweezer talks to Elbow, Elbow talks to Claude, Claude writes the code. It&amp;rsquo;s turtles all the way down.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="the-problem"&gt;The Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claude Code is an incredible coding agent — but it lives in the terminal as an interactive REPL. Tweezer sends messages on Telegram. How do we bridge the two? We needed nanobot to delegate coding tasks to Claude Code and get results back without anyone touching a keyboard.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>DuckDuckGo Timeout Fix</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/duckduckgo-timeout-fix/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/duckduckgo-timeout-fix/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Tool Call Timeouts</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/tool-call-timeouts/</link><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/tool-call-timeouts/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Atomic File Writes</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/atomic-file-writes/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/atomic-file-writes/</guid><description/></item><item><title>launchd Service Management</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/launchd-service-management/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/launchd-service-management/</guid><description/></item><item><title>LLM Model Fallback Chains</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/llm-model-fallback-chains/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/llm-model-fallback-chains/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Resilient JSONL Loading</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/resilient-jsonl-loading/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/resilient-jsonl-loading/</guid><description/></item><item><title>SSRF Whitelisting Localhost</t